trans-unit.source: The DsmlResponseDocument class is a read-only collection generated as a response to a <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlRequestDocument"></xref> object that contains zero, or more, objects derived from <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DirectoryResponse"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: A classe DsmlResponseDocument é uma coleção somente leitura gerada como uma resposta a uma <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlRequestDocument"> </xref> objeto que contém zero ou mais objetos derivados da <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DirectoryResponse"> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: The CopyTo method copies the entire collection to a one-dimensional array, starting at the specified index of the target array.
trans-unit.target: O método CopyTo copia toda a coleção para uma matriz unidimensional, começando no índice especificado da matriz de destino.

trans-unit.source: A one-dimensional array that is the destination of the elements copied from the <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlRequestDocument"></xref> object.
trans-unit.target: Uma matriz unidimensional que é o destino dos elementos copiados a partir de <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlRequestDocument"> </xref> objeto.

trans-unit.source: The zero-based index of `value` where copying begins.
trans-unit.target: O índice de base zero `value` onde a cópia começa.

trans-unit.source: value is a null reference ( in Visual Basic).
trans-unit.target: valueé uma referência nula ( no Visual Basic).

trans-unit.target: ié menor que zero.

trans-unit.source: The IsErrorResponse property specifies whether an error response has occurred.
trans-unit.target: A propriedade IsErrorResponse Especifica se uma resposta de erro ocorreu.

trans-unit.source: This property is <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if an error response has occurred; <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>, otherwise.

trans-unit.target: A propriedade IsOperationError Especifica se uma resposta de erro de operação ocorreu.

trans-unit.source: The SyncRoot property contains an object that can be used to synchronize access to the <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: A propriedade SyncRoot contém um objeto que pode ser usado para sincronizar o acesso a <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument"> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: Derived classes can provide synchronized versions of the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument> using the SyncRoot property.
trans-unit.target: Classes derivadas podem fornecer versões sincronizadas do <xref:System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument>usando a propriedade SyncRoot.</xref:System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument>

trans-unit.source: The synchronizing code must perform operations on the SyncRoot of the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument>, not directly on the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument>.
trans-unit.target: O código de sincronização deve executar operações no SyncRoot do <xref:System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument>, não diretamente no <xref:System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument>.</xref:System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument> </xref:System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument>

trans-unit.source: This ensures proper operation of collections derived from other objects.
trans-unit.target: Isso garante que a operação correta de coleções derivadas de outros objetos.

trans-unit.source: Specifically, it maintains proper synchronization with other threads that might be simultaneously modifying the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument> object.
trans-unit.target: Especificamente, ele mantém uma sincronização adequada com outros threads que podem ser simultaneamente modificando o <xref:System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument>objeto.</xref:System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DsmlResponseDocument>
